news.title: Guangzhou R&F Properties seeks to extend offshore bond maturity
news.para: The developer also proposed two options under a tender offer started on Wednesday: buying back the notes at a 17% discount, or $830 for every $1,000 in principal; or buying back at most half of a bondholder's notes in full, both with accrued interest.

news.title: China property market hit by more headwinds in November 2021
news.para: New home prices fell 0.3% month-on-month in November, the biggest decline since February 2015, according to Reuters calculations based on data released by the National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) on Wednesday. That was worse than the 0.2% drop in October.

news.title: Foreigners buy Turkish homes at record pace as lira slides
news.para: Against a background of more than 20% annual inflation, the property market was generally buoyant in November, with overall sales surging 59% year-on-year to 178,814 properties, the Turkish Statistical Institute figures showed.

news.title: Offshore Kaisa Group bondholders look to buy its China bad loans: Sources
news.para: Kaisa, which has offshore debt of $12 billion, did not repay $400 million of bonds that matured last week, triggering cross-default provision on all its offshore bonds and prompting a downgrade to "restricted default" by Fitch Ratings.

news.title: North Delhi civic body to auction 132 plots at Sanjay Gandhi Transport Nagar
news.para: According to the corporation, there are 132 plots of different sizes that have been identified for e-auctioning at Sanjay Gandhi Transport Nagar. These include community centre areas and land near a proposed railway line.

news.title: China audits Evergrande, chairman's assets, no fire sale for now: Sources
news.para: The audit, previously unreported, highlights how Beijing is taking charge at Evergrande after the real estate giant missed payments on two overseas bonds, triggering a restructuring to address Evergrande's more than $300 billion in liabilities.

news.title: Khunti tribals oppose centre's rural land-mapping scheme
news.para: The protesters demanded strict implementation of flagship regulations meant for tribal and Scheduled areas like PESA (Panchayat Extension of the Scheduled Areas) Act, CNT and SPT to restore sanctity in the tribal regions.

news.title: Coimbatore: Residents slam move to convert EB connection into commercial
news.para: The move comes after Tangedco officials found that the residential flats/apartments were using electricity lines meant for domestic purposes for reserve osmosis water treatment, fire hydrant system and sewage water treatment plants during their recent round of inspections.

news.title: Prestige Group, Awfis to invest Rs 70 crore to set-up six co-working centres
news.para: "We have already launched six centres in the first phase of our partnership with Prestige group. Now, we are going for the second phase of expansion," Awfis Founder and CEO Amit Ramani told PTI.

news.title: Maharashtra collection of stamp duty down 17% in November 2021
news.para: So far in this financial year, October had reported the highest collections. Officials say the dip in November was expected and was in line with the average revenue in the rest of the months.

news.title: Serve notice to Goa-SEIAA for sand mining nod: NGT
news.para: The Goa River Sand Protectors Network, functioning under the Goa Foundation, approached the tribunal against the Goa-SEIAA order stating that ‘there has been no due and proper application of mind before according environment clearance and hence prays for interference’.

news.title: Godrej Fund Management raises Rs 3,800 crore to build office buildings
news.para: "GFM will develop grade-A office assets that will be valued in excess of USD 1.5 billion (Rs 11,000 crore) on completion and the total value of the assets including those from previous funds will take the portfolio value on completion to over USD 3 billion (Rs 22,000 crore)," a company statement said.

news.title: Punjab cabinet gives nod for allotment of 25,000 EWS houses
news.para: The applications for these houses along with necessary documents would be invited from the eligible applicants as per the approved policy.

news.title: Greater Noida: Man arrested for putting up fake YEIDA land allotment ad
news.para: The main accused, Manoj Sharma, told police that he had created the advertisement with the help of one Suraj Kumar and put it on Facebook to make quick money.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh land survey model worth copying: Maharashtra government
news.para: A team of 11 senior officials led by Maharashtra survey settlement commissioner Niranjan Kumar Sudanshu is touring the state for the past two days to study the land survey project being implemented here.
